CrossEx AI
From Witness Statements to Cross-Examination Questions in Minutes
Anna-Native Litigation Intelligence Workflow
________________________________________
The Problem
Preparing for cross-examination is one of the most time-consuming tasks in litigation.
Lawyers must manually review witness statements, affidavits, complaints, and depositions to identify key facts, inconsistencies, omissions, and opportunities for cross-examination. This process often requires hours of reading and analysis before meaningful questions can be drafted.
Traditional AI chatbots can summarize documents, but they do not provide a structured litigation workflow that helps lawyers transform witness statements into reviewable cross-examination strategies.
________________________________________
The Solution
CrossEx AI is an Anna-native workflow that transforms witness statements into structured cross-examination preparation.
Instead of acting as a generic legal assistant, CrossEx AI focuses on one specific workflow:
Witness Statement → Fact Extraction → Contradiction Analysis → Cross-Examination Questions → Lawyer Review
The system helps legal professionals quickly identify key facts, highlight potential inconsistencies, and generate targeted cross-examination questions while maintaining complete human control over the final output.
________________________________________
How It Works
Step 1: Upload or Paste Witness Statement
The lawyer uploads or pastes a witness statement, affidavit, or complaint.
Step 2: Fact Extraction
CrossEx AI extracts material facts and organizes them into a structured timeline.
Step 3: Contradiction & Weakness Analysis
The system identifies:
•	Internal inconsistencies
•	Missing information
•	Ambiguous assertions
•	Potential credibility issues
Step 4: Question Generation
The AI generates:
•	Fact-confirmation questions
•	Credibility-testing questions
•	Contradiction-focused questions
•	Timeline verification questions
Step 5: Human Review
Questions remain editable and reviewable.
Nothing is finalized without lawyer approval.
________________________________________
Why It Is AI-Native
CrossEx AI is not a chatbot.
The AI participates in a structured legal workflow by:
•	Extracting facts
•	Analyzing witness narratives
•	Identifying inconsistencies
•	Generating litigation-ready questions
Human review remains a mandatory step before any output is used.
________________________________________
